name: Flexi-disc
description: Flexi-discs are phonograph records made of a thin, flexible vinyl sheet with a molded-in groove, designed to be playable on a normal phonograph turntable.

name: Shellac
description: Shellac records were the most predominant type of gramophone record during the first half of the 20th century.

name: VHD
description: Video High Density (VHD) was a videodisc format which was marketed predominantly in Japan by JVC.

name: Pathé disc
description: 90 rpm, vertical-cut shellac discs, produced by the Pathé label from 1906 to 1932.

name: CED
description: The Capacitance Electronic Disc (CED) is an analog video disc playback system developed by RCA, in which video and audio could be played back on a TV set using a special needle and high-density groove system similar to phonograph records.

name: Copy Control CD
description: Copy Control CD (CCCD) is an umbrella term for CDs released circa 2001-2006 containing software that is ostensibly designed to prevent the CD from being ripped. There are a number of software variants: the most well-known are Macrovision's Cactus Data Shield (CDS) and SunnComm's MediaMax.

name: Hybrid SACD (CD layer)
description: The CD layer of a hybrid SACD. The SACD layer should be added as a separate medium.

name: Hybrid SACD (SACD layer)
description: The SACD layer of a hybrid SACD. The CD layer should be added as a separate medium.

name: DualDisc (DVD-Audio side)
description: The DVD (audio) layer of a DualDisc. The CD layer should be added as a separate medium.

name: DualDisc (DVD-Video side)
description: The DVD (video) layer of a DualDisc. The CD layer should be added as a separate medium.

name: DualDisc (CD side)
description: The CD layer of a DualDisc. The DVD layer should be added as a separate medium.

name: DVDplus (DVD-Audio side)
description: The DVD (audio) layer of a DVDplus. The CD layer should be added as a separate medium.

name: DVDplus (DVD-Video side)
description: The DVD (audio) layer of a DVDplus. The CD layer should be added as a separate medium.

name: DVDplus (CD side)
description: The CD layer of a DVDplus. The DVD layer should be added as a separate medium.
